 :tx/rationale "Create task: AR-2 (REVISED): Session trace buffer + harvest flush — in-memory Vec<Datom> written to store once at harvest, not per-command (INV-STORE-014, INV-HARVEST-001, INV-GUIDANCE-024). BACKGROUND: Original AR-2 wrote :recon/trace datoms on every command — violating read-command cache invariant (50ms churn per read). REVISED: traces accumulate in a session-scoped in-memory buffer (Vec<TraceDatom>). The buffer is thread-local state in main.rs (or passed through BudgetCtx). At harvest, the buffer is committed as a single transaction. During the session, the concentration detector reads from the buffer directly (zero IO cost). This is the Stage 1 precursor to Working Set W_alpha (INV-STORE-013, Stage 2). APPROACH: (1) Define SessionTraceBuffer struct: traces: Vec<TraceDatom> where TraceDatom = { spec_refs: Vec<String>, neighbors: Vec<EntityId>, neighborhood: String, command: String, tx_ordinal: usize }. (2) In main.rs: create SessionTraceBuffer at startup. After each command, call buffer.record(cmd_output, store) which extracts spec refs from JSON, runs spec_graph_neighbors, and pushes a TraceDatom. No store write. (3) In harvest pipeline: call buffer.flush_to_datoms(tx) -> Vec<Datom> to convert buffer to :recon/* datoms for the harvest transaction. (4) Wire buffer into concentration detector: spec_neighborhood_concentration reads from &SessionTraceBuffer, not from store. (5) Schema: add :recon/* attributes (same as before) but they only appear in harvest transactions, not per-command. ACCEPTANCE: (A) braid status (read command) does NOT modify store. (B) braid harvest --commit includes :recon/trace datoms from session buffer. (C) Concentration detector works from buffer during session. (D) After harvest, :recon/trace datoms are queryable in store. (E) Buffer persists across commands within a single CLI process (typical: one command per process, but harvest sees the full session via store reload). CONSIDERATION: Since each CLI invocation is a separate process, the buffer doesn't persist across invocations. The concentration detector must work from BOTH the in-memory buffer (current process) AND stored :recon/trace datoms (previous commands in this session). This means: at startup, load recent :recon/trace datoms from store into the buffer, then append new traces, then flush at harvest. DEPENDS-ON: AR-1. FILE: crates/braid/src/main.rs + crates/braid-kernel/src/guidance.rs + crates/braid/src/commands/harvest.rs"
